modules.description: This module enables configuration parameter definition and parsing with type-safe value conversion, command-line interface setup, and documentation generation. It operates on basic types like integers and strings, extended to files, directories, enums, and container types such as lists and tuples, using customizable separators and formatting. It is suited for command-line argument processing, configuration file interpretation, and maintaining structured parameter documentation with deprecation handling.

This module defines configuration parameters for controlling output behavior, including monitors, output destination, rule sets, and traceback depth. It works with string lists, optional strings, and optional integers to configure logging and analysis settings. Concrete use cases include setting output file paths, enabling specific analysis monitors, and limiting traceback depth for debugging.
